<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="90">1.8. Images</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>First, you’ll upload images of the item and its variations here. For example, you could upload images of a t-shirt in red, blue and green.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Then you’ll assign the images to the appropriate variations. This causes customers e.g. to automatically see an image of the green t-shirt when selecting this variation in the online store.</p>
</div>
<h4 id="_uploading_images" class="discrete">Uploading images</h4>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Uploading an item image:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Edit item</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><a href="/en/item/introduction/search#100">Search for</a> and open the item.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Images</strong> tab in the upper row.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Drag &amp; drop images into the appropriate area or click on <span class="icon purple"><i class="psicon-upload"></i></span> <strong>Select files</strong> and upload the images.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the additional settings. Note <a href="#table-upload-item-image">Table 3</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<table id="table-upload-item-image" class="tableblock frame-all grid-all stretch">
