<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Specify the type of picking. If you do not want to define the order picking type, select the empty option.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Main warehouse</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Select the variation’s main warehouse.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Pallet type</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Select the pallet type.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Packing units</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Select the number of packing units and the type of packaging if the item consists of multiple packages.<br>
Select the value <strong>0</strong> if you always want the item to be shipped in a single package, regardless of the quantity. This setting also applies to various items. This means that all items of an order that have the value <strong>0</strong> will be packed into one package.</p></td>
</tr>
